        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 6:04PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Dutton, or 22 miles northwest of Great Falls, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Knees.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
